ywright of the year (2019)\n|parents       = Jiban Dey , Rina Dey\n|children      = \n|partner       = \n|spouse        = \n|notableworks  = \n|movement      = \n|subject       = \n|genre         = \n|period        = \n|education     = MA Economics, MA Journalism\n|image         = Rajdweep.jpg\n|language      = [[Assamese language|Assamese]], [[Hindi]], [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n|occupation    = Screenwriter, playwright, lyricist, journalist\n|death_place   = \n|death_date    = \n|birth_place   = [[Dhing, Nagaon, Assam]], India\n|birth_date    = {{birth-date and age|20 September 1986}}\n|birth_name    = \n|pseudonym     = \n|caption       = Rajdweep receiving award at Cinestaan India's Biggest Script Contest in 2018\n|alt           = \n|imagesize     = 200px\n|website       = {{url|www.rajdweep.com}}\n}}\n'''Rajdweep''' is an award-winning Indian screenwriter, playwright, lyricist and journalist hails from [[Dhing, Nagaon, Assam]].<ref name=Cinestaan>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/articles/2019/feb/10/18581/playwright-rajdweep-on-how-the-universe-conspired-to-help-him-win-a-cinestaan-script-contest-prize/amp|title=Playwright Rajdweep on how the universe conspired to help him win a Cinestaan script contest prize|website=www.cinestaan.com| access-date= 6 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guwahatiplus.com/buzz/assamese-playwright-rajdweep-wins-best-play-of-the-year-award.amp|title=Assamese playwright Rajdweep wins \"Best Play of the Year\" award|website=Guwahati Plus| access-date= 6 December 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"drongoexpress.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.drongoexpress.com/2018/12/05/script-by-assams-rajdweep-wins-heart-of-aamir-khan-rajkumar-hirani/|title=Script by Assam's Rajdweep wins heart of Aamir Khan, Rajkumar Hirani|website=drongoexpress| access-date= 6 December 2019}}</ref> He has been awarded by Bollywood superstar [[Aamir Khan]] for his script 'Ishqlogy' at Cinestaan India's Storyteller's Script Contest in 2018.<ref name=Cinestaan/><ref name=\"drongoexpress.com\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.assamtribune.com/scripts/detailsnew.asp?id=nov3018/city060|title=Scriptwriter Rajdweep placed fourth in 'Storytellers Contest'|website=The Assam Tribune| access-date= 7 December 2019}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musianacollective.org/the-man-with-mighty-pen/|title=The mighty pen of a young writer makes Assam proud {{!}} Musiana Collective|last=N|first=Jolly|last2=Sarkar|first2=i|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref>He has been the first lyricist from Assam who writes Assamese songs in Bollywood film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenewsmill.com/first-time-full-length-assamese-song-bollywood-film/|title=For the first time: A full-length Assamese song in a Bollywood film|date=2017-07-03|website=The News Mill|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref> He has written songs like 'Jiri Jiri' for [[Konkona Sen Sharma]] directed film \n''[[A Death In The Gunj]]'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/when-bollywood-goes-jirijiri-to-assam-beats/cid/1434934|title=When Bollywood goes jirijiri to Assam beats|website=www.telegraphindia.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.assamtribune.com/scripts/detailsnew.asp?id=jul0717/city058|title=The Assam Tribune Online|website=www.assamtribune.com|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref> and the bihu song for [[Anurag Basu]] directed film ''[[Jagga Jasoos]]''. Again, he becomes the first screenwriter from Assam who signed a Bollywood film. He signed the film on 21 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.time8.in/new-playwright-rajdweep-all-set-to-debut-in-bollywood/|title=Playwright Rajdweep All Set To Debut In Bollywood|date=2019-10-22|website=TIME8|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.magzter.com/article/Lifestyle/Eclectic-Northeast/Scripting-The-Bollywood-Dream|title=Scripting The Bollywood Dream|website=www.magzter.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n\n== Personal Life and Education ==\nRajdweep was born on 20 September 1986 in [[Nagaon]], [[Assam]]. After doing graduation in Economics from Gauhati University, Rajdweep did Masters in Economics and then completed his Masters in Journalism.\n\n== Career==\n\nAfter working in many Assamese films, albums & plays, Rajdweep made his Bollywood debut in the [[Konkona Sen Sharma]] directed film ''[[A Death in the Gunj]]'' (2016) as a lyricist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/when-bollywood-goes-jirijiri-to-assam-beats/cid/1434934|title=When Bollywood goes jirijiri to Assam beats|website=Telegraph India|access-date= 6 December 2019}}</ref> His song 'Jiri Jiri' was an Assamese song in the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.uniindia.com/assamese-song-in-a-bollywood-movie/-regional/fullstory/919252.html|title=Assamese song in a Bollywood Movie|website=United News of India|access-date= 7 December 2019}}</ref> He has been credited for writing the first full-length Assamese song in any Bollywood film. After that, he again got the opportunity to write a song for [[Anurag Basu]] directed film ''[[Jagga Jasoos]]''. He wrote the Bihu song 'Lahe Lahe' for this film. Before that, for MTV dewarist show, he penned the widely accepted song called 'Memories' with Papon and Nucleya. His Hindi songs are 'Pakhi Pakhi', 'Aao Kabhi Jo'. As a screenwriter, Rajdweep's first film was ''Khel-the Game'' (2015). His other film as screenplay writer ''Rum Vodka Whisky'' has been released across Assam. Rajdweep has written songs in lots of Assamese films and various albums, theatre plays. As the youngest playwright of Assam's unique mobile theatre industry, Rajdweep has written many full-length plays.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/3d-to-brighten-kohinoor-glow/cid/1415060?ref=search-page|title=3D to brighten Kohinoor glow|website=Telegraph India|access-date= 7 December 2019}}</ref> Apart from these, Rajdweep has a career in professional journalism and he is working as senior sub-editor of a vernacular daily called 'Assamiya Khabar'. He was conferred with the 2018-19 'Best Play of the Year' award for his play, ''Bondookor Kobita'' by All Assam Sahitya Sanmilan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guwahatiplus.com/buzz/assamese-playwright-rajdweep-wins-best-play-of-the-year-award.amp|title=Assamese playwright Rajdweep wins the best play of the year award|website=Guwahati Plus| access-date= 6 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and recognitions==\n[[File:Rajdweep with Aamir Khan.jpg|thumb|Rajdweep receiving award from Bollywood Superstar Aamir Khan for his script in Mumbai, 2018.]]\n*Awarded Assam State Film Award (Dr. Nirmalprabha Bordoloi Memorial Award) for Best Lyricist for the film ''Dooronir Nirola Poja'' (2017).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/magazine/anniversary-issue/story/20181231-stage-craft-young-leaders-1415590-2018-12-23|title=Stage Craft: Young Leaders: One of Assam's most successful playwright, director, one of Dey's scripts was recently awarded by a jury that included Aamir Khan and Rajkumar Hirani.|website=India Today| access-date= 6 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodcouch.com/india-today-features-screenwriter-rajdweep-as-young-leader-for-his-journey-from-mobile-theatre-to-cinestaan-contest-win/|title=India Today Features Screenwriter Rajdweep As 'Young Leader' For His Journey From Mobile Theatre To Cinestaan Contest Win!|website=www.bollywoodcouch.com|access-date= 7 December 2019}}</ref>\n* 4th Award Winner at India's Biggest Script Contest by Cinestaan (2018). Awarded by Bollywood Superster Aamir Khan on 26 November, at Novotel Hotel, Juhu, Mumbai. [[Aamir Khan]], [[Rajkumar Hirani]], [[Anjum Rajabali]], [[Juhi Chaturvedi]] were the jury members of this mega contest with around 4000 contestants from different parts of India. Rajdweep's script 'Ishqlogy - Something greater than technology' won the 4th prize. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/aamir-khan-announces-the-winners-of-the-first-edition-of-cinestaan-india-s-storytellers-script-contest-news-bollywood-sl2rmjibahgbh.html|title=Aamir Khan announces the winners of the first edition of Cinestaan India's Storytellers Script Contest|website=Sify|language=en|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://businessofcinema.com/bollywood_news/aamir-khan-felicitates-assamese-talent-rajdweep-for-his-script-ishqlogy/426264|title=Aamir Khan Felicitates Assamese Talent Rajdweep For His Script Ishqlogy|last=Network|first=BusinessofCinema News|date=2018-12-02|website=Businessofcinema.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news24hrs.in/?p=7042|title=Rajdweep, small town boy from Assam wins Aamir Khan's heart with his script 'Ishqlogy'|website=News 24 Hours|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref>\n* [[India Today]] featured him as 'Young Leader'. The leading news magazine of India featured Rajdweep for his journey from unique [[Mobile theatre in Assam]] to Bollywood.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodcouch.com/india-today-features-screenwriter-rajdweep-as-young-leader-for-his-journey-from-mobile-theatre-to-cinestaan-contest-win/|title=India Today features Screenwriter Rajdweep as 'Young Leader' for his journey from mobile theatre to Cinestaan Contest Win!|last=Patil -|first=Akshay|date=2019-01-04|website=Bollywood Couch|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/anniversary-issue/story/20181231-stage-craft-young-leaders-1415590-2018-12-23|title=Stage Craft {{!}} Young Leaders|last=December 23|first=Kaushik Deka New Delhi|last2=December 31|first2=2018 ISSUE DATE|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17|last3=December 25|first3=2018UPDATED|last4=Ist|first4=2018 13:08}}</ref>\n* Best Playwright Award for his play 'Bandookor Kobita' at Oikyotaan Award by  Asom Sahitya Sanmilani Award (2019).<ref>{{